        "content": "<p>Does <strong>hapi-fhir-cli</strong> work with the OpenJDK implementation of Java?</p>",
        "id": 153835923,
        "sender_full_name": "Gaston Fiore",
        "timestamp": 1467318818
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We use java-8 (openjdk) -- see <a href=\"https://github.com/sync-for-science/reference-stack-docker/blob/master/docker-builds/reference-api/Dockerfile\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/sync-for-science/reference-stack-docker/blob/master/docker-builds/reference-api/Dockerfile\">https://github.com/sync-for-science/reference-stack-docker/blob/master/docker-builds/reference-api/Dockerfile</a> for example</p>",
        "id": 153835927,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Mandel",
        "timestamp": 1467320632
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre> java -version\nopenjdk version &quot;1.8.0_66-internal&quot;\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_66-internal-b17)\nOpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.66-b17, mixed mode)\n</pre></div>",
        "id": 153835929,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Mandel",
        "timestamp": 1467320663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And for any docker fans out there (maybe someone already has created this functionality?) you can do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre>$ docker run --rm -it syncforscience/reference-api\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>To spin up a HAPI CLI server on localhost:8080</p>",
        "id": 153835931,
        "sender_full_name": "Josh Mandel",
        "timestamp": 1467320746
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It does require a minimum of Java 8 though FYI, unlike the rest of HAPI (which only requires Java 6)</p>",
